Python code for the electrocuting practice robot found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=daVxsP4wIDw

A lot of the code was "borrowed" from Allen Pans Zelda Ocarina Controlled Home Automation video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=glZnkpIDWSE
His How To Make The Zelda Ocarina Controlled Home Automation System here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1RzXoieos5Y

To use for different songs, you need to create the correct sequence of notes for that particular song.
And you must change the if statements that determining what note is currently being played to include only the notes in the song you have sequenced.

A bit of fine tuning of your mic placement, the instrument and the frequenct ranges may be required to get it working perfectly.
